# Custom Pages Multiplayer Spec

## Scope

Fine-grained live reconciliation for multiple users editing/viewing the same
custom page.

## Load when

Changing `PageBuilder`, page section state, save debounce, `usePageData`,
section registry validation, or page WebSocket handling.

## Owns

| File | Contract |
| --- | --- |
| `frontend/src/components/page/PageBuilder.tsx` | `mergeSections`, `stableStringify`, save pipeline |
| `frontend/src/components/page/BlockRenderer.tsx` | memoized section rendering |
| `frontend/src/hooks/usePageData.ts` | live page events, refresh, edit guard |
| `frontend/src/components/page/SaveStatusBar.tsx` | held incoming-change status |
| `frontend/src/components/page/PageBuilderContext.tsx` | `editingCount`, `enterEdit`, `leaveEdit` |
| `backend/internal/s_registry` | canonical section/component registry |
| `frontend/src/components/page/typedSectionApi.ts` | normalized mutation adapter and revision state |

## Reconciliation Contract

- All page updates, including a user's own save response and other users' WS
  pushes, pass through `mergeSections(current, incoming)`.
- `mergeSections` matches by section `id`.
- Unchanged sections keep old object references so `React.memo` can skip rerender.
- Equality uses `stableStringify`, which recursively sorts object keys to match
  PostgreSQL JSONB key-order normalization.
- Compare sections with `items` normalized to `[]` so local `undefined` and DB
  empty arrays do not appear different.
- On typed-ready pages, the backend response refreshes the stable server-ID and
  revision map. Debounced writes diff against the last authoritative document,
  so unchanged sections are not resubmitted and different-section writes retain
  independent expected revisions.

## Incoming Edit Guard

- `enterEdit`/`leaveEdit` maintain an editing count for active rich editors,
  sliders, code editors, and similar controls.
- While `editingCount > 0`, incoming `page_updated` data is held instead of
  applied immediately.
- Save debounce waits for all editors to leave, then flushes after the configured
  pause.
- When editing reaches zero, pending incoming data refreshes/applies through the
  same section merge path.

## Memo Chain

The section skip path depends on stable references across:

1. `mergeSections`
2. wrapper callbacks such as `updateSectionWrapper`
3. `React.memo(BlockRenderer)`
4. `React.memo(SectionBlock)`
5. memoized move context and ref-backed move handlers

Breaking any link can make every section rerender on every save/push.

## Backend Registry Contract

- `GET /config/sections` lists supported section types.
- `GET /config/section-types/{type}` returns one section definition.
- Page saves reject content that is not a JSON section array, omits
  `section_type`, or uses an unsupported type.
- Positive `derived_section.config.datasource_id` must resolve to a saved data
  source.
- Positive `custom_section.config.custom_section_id` must resolve to a saved
  custom section.
- Empty integration refs are allowed for drafts.
- `PAGE_TYPED_SECTION_MUTATIONS` is necessary but not sufficient: a page exposes
  typed writes only when its shadow parity status is `matched`.

## Invariants

- No `ownSavePendingRef` skip path; own saves also normalize through merge.
- Backend `page_updated` excludes the sender because the HTTP response is already
  authoritative for that user.
- Incoming broadcasts do not carry user-specific `is_liked` / `can_delete`; keep
  local values when applying page data.
- Cancel queued save timers and clear pending sections before page or landing swaps.
- Section sync bails out while unsaved local sections or active editors exist.
- Structural typed mutations flush earlier debounced section edits first.
- Same-section `409` conflicts trigger an explanatory error and authoritative
  refetch; reconnect replay also forces a refetch of page revisions.

